profile.summary:
Co-founder of TechVariable, an end-to-end product development company catered to tech startups. Successfully delivered MVPs in 2x quicker time. Acquired expertise in building, managing, and subsequently proliferating strong offshore product development teams. Firmly follows the Offshore Delivery model, with a special focus on establishing governance frameworks for effective project management and delivery. 

Have set up dedicated product development teams for clients through our services like Product planning (PRD), Interaction Designing & Architecture (UI-UX design), Custom Application Development (Product Engineering), and Deployment.

experience.description:
TechVariable is an end-to-end rapid Product Development company for startups who are looking to get their MVPs/Products released in the market faster. Core services include Product planning (PRD), Interaction Designing & Architecture (UI-UX design), Custom Application Development (Product Engineering), and Deployment (DevOps).

We have a team that has garnered experience over its 5+ years of journey in developing end-to-end products for our clients in multiple domains. We start off the development cycle by working on the scope for an MVP so that a market-fit product can be delivered within the initially assigned budget and timeline. Once the MVP is released in the market and user feedbacks received, our product engineering team makes sure that we deliver the best possible sequences of releases throughout the product lifecycle. Right from seeding to feeding, we make sure that we remain the development partners for our clients and not just another outsourcing vendor.

experience.description:
My responsibilities include:
- Getting aquainted to the prevailing techology based products and understand their technicality (basically the torque converter components)
- Major project was the FEA analysis of a rectangular riveted joint used in back plate of a pendulum absorber assembly. First, the riveting process was simulated using the bulk forming FEA software like FORGE and then fatigue analysis was performed on the joint post-riveting. The main aim was to establish a methodology for this kind of analysis so that the effect of residual stresses induced during riveting can be included in the fatigue analysis.
- Live projects completion from clients - 1) Performing static analysis on a riveted joint for a torque converter (drive plate and hub assembly) to ensure the joint can endure a given number of cycle, 2) Meshing of various parts of torque converter. etc.

publications.name: Design Optmisation of a riveted joint used in back plate of a pendulum absorber assembly
publications.publisher: STM journals- Recent Trends in Mechanical Engineering-
publications.description: Riveted joints are widely used for fastening sheet metal components. Cylindrical rivets are generally preferred but due to space constraints in some cases, other geometries are being explored. In this work, a practical case of a rectangular riveted assembly for back plate of pendulum absorber assembly commonly used in modern vehicles for damping secondary vibrations is considered and an iterative simulation study for design optimization has been conducted using finite element based software FORGE for the riveting process. Efficacy of riveted joints is analyzed in terms of Von-Mises stresses, tonnage and contact pressure. Out of the many design parameters, only prominent parameters like variation of fillet radius in the plate hole and rivet and the distance between the hole and the side of the plate were concentrated upon. An attempt is made to change the values of these design parameters to arrive at an optimum design criterion for the riveted joint so that the stress induced is minimized to a value that can be considered to be within permissible limits. It is found out by iterative simulation studies that the maximum stress induced got reduced by 23.2% with a square rivet as compared to a rectangular rivet.
